---
title: Hearty Pork Chili with Kidney Beans and Poblano Peppers
description: It doesn’t matter if the weather’s hot or cool where you are—it’s chili season! In this version, we’re keeping things simmering with ground pork, kidney beans, poblano peppers, and our special Mexican spice blend, which has just the tiniest bit of heat. It’s mild enough for your kids to gobble up but has plenty of flavor to satisfy the adults. Break out the hot sauce if you like it scorching.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5a9589aeae08b52fac24c282-96387303.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/hearty-pork-chili-5a9589aeae08b52fac24c282-68ab43c7.pdf
course: main course
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
time required: 30 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 660 kcal
  fat: 38 g
  saturated fat: 15 g
  carbohydrates: 40 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 42 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 1030 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/hearty-pork-chili-5a9589aeae08b52fac24c282
---

Wash and dry all produce. Thinly slice @scallions{4}, keeping greens and whites separate. Mince or grate @garlic{4%cloves}. Drain and rinse @kidney beans{1%box}. Core and seed @poblano peppers{2}, then cut into ½-inch squares.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground pork{20%oz} and @Mexican spice blend{2%tbsp}, breaking up meat into pieces. Cook, stirring occasionally, until crisped at the edges and no longer pink, ~{4-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove from #pan{} and set aside.

Add a drizzle of @vegetable oil{}, scallion whites, poblanos, and garlic to same pan. Cook, tossing, until lightly browned and softened, about ~{5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir @chicken stock concentrate{2}, beans, @crushed tomatoes{2%box}, and @water{1/2%cup} into pan. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and let simmer until slightly thickened, about ~{5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Return pork and any drippings to pan. Simmer until saucy and very thick, about ~{5%minutes} longer.

Divide chili between #bowls{}. Sprinkle with @cheddar cheese{1%cup} and scallion greens. Dollop with @sour cream{8%tbsp} and serve.

> It doesn't matter if the weather's hot or cool where you are—it's chili season! In this version, we're keeping things simmering with ground pork, kidney beans, poblano peppers, and our special Mexican spice blend, which has just the tiniest bit of heat. It's mild enough for your kids to gobble up but has plenty of flavor to satisfy the adults. Break out the hot sauce if you like it scorching.